Appendix B: Algorithm 1 – 2D‑MFDFA (Pseudocode)

```
Input: Binary vessel mask I (size M×N), q_list = [-5,-4,...,5], s_list = [8,16,32,64,128]
Output: phi vector of length 18 (D_0, h(q) for each q, Δα, Λ_5, Λ_10, Λ_20)

1. Compute mean value ⟨I⟩ = (1/(M N)) Σ_i Σ_j I(i,j)
2. Compute cumulative surface U(i,j) = Σ_{k=1}^i Σ_{l=1}^j (I(k,l) - ⟨I⟩)
3. For each s in s_list:
   a. M_s = floor(M/s), N_s = floor(N/s)
   b. For each box (v,w) in 1..M_s, 1..N_s:
        Extract submatrix U_box of size s×s at offset (v*s, w*s)
        Fit 2nd order polynomial p(i,j) = a0 + a1*i + a2*j + a3*i*j + a4*i^2 + a5*j^2
        Compute residual variance F2(v,w,s) = (1/s^2) Σ_i Σ_j (U_box(i,j) - p(i,j))^2
   c. For each q in q_list:
        If q != 0:
            F_q(s) = ( (1/(M_s N_s)) Σ_v Σ_w (F2(v,w,s))^(q/2) )^(1/q)
        Else:
            F_q(s) = exp( (1/(M_s N_s)) Σ_v Σ_w log(F2(v,w,s)) )
4. For each q, perform linear regression of log(F_q(s)) vs log(s) to obtain h(q)
5. Compute τ(q) = q*h(q) - 2
6. Compute α(q) = τ'(q) (using finite differences) and f(α) = q*α - τ(q)
   Obtain Δα = max(α) - min(α)
7. Set D_0 = h(0)
8. Compute lacunarity:
   For each r in [5,10,20]:
        Slide a box of size r×r over I (stride 1)
        For each box, compute mass M = number of vessel pixels
        Compute histogram P(M,r) = fraction of boxes with mass M
        Compute Z1 = Σ_M M P(M,r), Z2 = Σ_M M^2 P(M,r)
        Λ_r = Z2 / (Z1^2)
9. Return phi = [D_0, h(-5),...,h(5), Δα, Λ_5, Λ_10, Λ_20]
```

